ns0:Concept.displayName: Dual-energy X-ray absorptiometry (DXA), bone density study, 1 or more sites; appendicular skeleton (peripheral) (eg, radius, wrist, heel)

ns0:DescribedValueSet.ns0:Purpose: (Clinical Focus: Peripheral xray study to determine bone density),(Data Element Scope: The intent of this data element is to identify patients with low bone mineral density.),(Inclusion Criteria: Appendicular skeleton (radius, wrist, heel)),(Exclusion Criteria: 1 or more sites, axial skeleton (hips, pelvis, spine))
